    caption: [The formation of DHT (dihydrotestosterone). Testosterone secreted by interstitial (Leydig) cells of the testes is converted to DHT within target cells through addition of hydrogen and removal of a double bond, catalyzed by 5α-reductase enzyme.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
  ),
