    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
  ),
  "20-13": (
    caption: [Derivatives of testosterone. Testosterone from interstitial (Leydig) cells is converted to active metabolites in brain and target organs, including DHT (dihydrotestosterone) and estradiol, which mediate different physiological effects.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
  ),
  "table-20-4": (
